this doesn't really

00:27:32.550 --> 00:27:33.840
make sense, because this
thing is an operator.

00:27:33.840 --> 00:27:34.790
That's not a quantity.

00:27:34.790 --> 00:27:36.000
Quantity is something
you measure.

00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:36.958
So what do you measure?

00:27:36.958 --> 00:27:39.130
Do you measure the operator?

00:27:39.130 --> 00:27:42.394
In a state, you measure
its expectation values.

00:27:42.394 --> 00:27:43.810
You might measure
its eigenvalues,

00:27:43.810 --> 00:27:48.450
but the more general thing
is expectation values.

00:27:48.450 --> 00:27:50.640
So this is something
that depends on time,

00:27:50.640 --> 00:27:53.660
because the wave function
depends on time-- psi of t.

00:27:53.660 --> 00:27:56.390
OK, so the best to say
something is conserved,

00:27:56.390 --> 00:27:58.863
is to say d dt of A is 0.

00:28:01.790 --> 00:28:03.660
But we've seen
what the condition

00:28:03.660 --> 00:28:08.200
