00:30:29.555 --> 00:30:30.430
You can't know three.

00:30:30.430 --> 00:30:32.559
You can know the total
angular momentum, little l.

00:30:32.559 --> 00:30:34.100
And you can know
the angular momentum

00:30:34.100 --> 00:30:36.183
in a particular direction,
which we conventionally

00:30:36.183 --> 00:30:37.862
call z-- little n, right?

00:30:37.862 --> 00:30:39.820
But you can't know some
other angular momentum,

00:30:39.820 --> 00:30:41.770
like angular momentum in x
direction simultaneously.

00:30:41.770 --> 00:30:42.720
So what does it mean
to say that there

00:30:42.720 --> 00:30:43.960
are three conserved quantities?

00:30:43.960 --> 00:30:46.335
I can't know three conserved
quantities at the same time.

00:30:46.335 --> 00:30:48.640
They're not even well defined
at some moment in time.

00:30:48.640 --> 00:30:51.400
