three operators-- lx,

00:30:51.400 --> 00:30:54.870
and ly, and lz--
which I will simply

00:30:54.870 --> 00:31:00.200
write as l vector-- all of
which commute with E. So

00:31:00.200 --> 00:31:04.510
while it's true that
systems don't have

00:31:04.510 --> 00:31:07.460
definite values of lx,
ly and lz simultaneously,

00:31:07.460 --> 00:31:09.730
nonetheless lx, ly
and lz all commute

00:31:09.730 --> 00:31:11.245
with the energy operator.

00:31:11.245 --> 00:31:13.370
And as a consequence, their
time expectation values

00:31:13.370 --> 00:31:15.657
are all 0 in a
central potential.

00:31:15.657 --> 00:31:17.490
So the time derivatives
of their expectation

00:31:17.490 --> 00:31:18.890
are all 0s in a
central potential.

00:31:18.890 --> 00:31:20.723
They're all constant
in a central potential.

00:31:20.723 --> 00:31:21.854
Yeah.

